</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1324,2034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,501,1397,1422]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">Head and thorax (color).</emphasis>
Color pattern very similar to that in 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Li" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Li" box="[931,1318,1397,1422]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamata">
<emphasis box="[931,1172,1397,1421]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">Japanagallia hamata</emphasis>
Zhang &amp; Li
</taxonomicName>
excepting spots on crown fused with each other forming black band, and legs with larger black areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1324,2034]" box="[199,935,1469,1494]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1469,1494]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">Morphology.</emphasis>
Similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Li" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Li" box="[477,729,1469,1494]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamata">
<emphasis box="[477,489,1470,1493]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">J</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[504,588,1469,1493]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">hamata</emphasis>
Zhang &amp; Li
</taxonomicName>
, but more slender.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1324,2034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,380,1505,1530]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">Male genitalia:</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[496,581,1505,1530]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 30" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1588,1612]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,364,1562]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,347,1565]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 30. Japanagallia neohamata sp. nov. Male: (22 – 23) Habitus: (22) dorsal, and (23) lateral views; (24) face; (25) genital capsule, subgenital plates, and anal tube, lateral view; (26) pygofer posterior margins, caudal view; (27) style, dorsal view; (28) connective, dorsal view; aedeagus (29) lateral, and (30) dorsal views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228240/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">
Fig. 
<number box="[550,581,1505,1530]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, broad basally, caudal margin subrounded, with spine-like processes caudodorsally (
<figureCitation box="[441,524,1541,1566]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 30" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1588,1612]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,364,1562]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,347,1565]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 30. Japanagallia neohamata sp. nov. Male: (22 – 23) Habitus: (22) dorsal, and (23) lateral views; (24) face; (25) genital capsule, subgenital plates, and anal tube, lateral view; (26) pygofer posterior margins, caudal view; (27) style, dorsal view; (28) connective, dorsal view; aedeagus (29) lateral, and (30) dorsal views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228240/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">
Fig. 
<number box="[495,524,1541,1566]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139" value="26.0">26</number>
</figureCitation>
) directed mesally, and several stout and short setae. Valve and subgenital plates (
<figureCitation box="[159,245,1577,1602]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 30" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1588,1612]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,364,1562]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,347,1565]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 30. Japanagallia neohamata sp. nov. Male: (22 – 23) Habitus: (22) dorsal, and (23) lateral views; (24) face; (25) genital capsule, subgenital plates, and anal tube, lateral view; (26) pygofer posterior margins, caudal view; (27) style, dorsal view; (28) connective, dorsal view; aedeagus (29) lateral, and (30) dorsal views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228240/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">
Fig. 
<number box="[214,245,1577,1602]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zhang &amp; Li. Style" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Li. Style" box="[559,891,1577,1602]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamata">
<emphasis box="[559,571,1578,1601]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">J</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[588,672,1577,1601]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">hamata</emphasis>
Zhang &amp; Li. Style
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[908,994,1577,1602]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 30" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1588,1612]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,364,1562]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,347,1565]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 30. Japanagallia neohamata sp. nov. Male: (22 – 23) Habitus: (22) dorsal, and (23) lateral views; (24) face; (25) genital capsule, subgenital plates, and anal tube, lateral view; (26) pygofer posterior margins, caudal view; (27) style, dorsal view; (28) connective, dorsal view; aedeagus (29) lateral, and (30) dorsal views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228240/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">
Fig. 
<number box="[963,994,1578,1602]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139" value="27.0">27</number>
</figureCitation>
), constricted at middle, expanded, and bearing a 
<taxonomicName box="[260,363,1613,1638]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Japanagallia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="139" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lamellate">lamellate</taxonomicName>
process subapically on outer margin, apex of inner arm slightly expanded. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1423,1613,1638]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 30" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1588,1612]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,364,1562]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,347,1565]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 30. Japanagallia neohamata sp. nov. Male: (22 – 23) Habitus: (22) dorsal, and (23) lateral views; (24) face; (25) genital capsule, subgenital plates, and anal tube, lateral view; (26) pygofer posterior margins, caudal view; (27) style, dorsal view; (28) connective, dorsal view; aedeagus (29) lateral, and (30) dorsal views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228240/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1423,1614,1638]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139" value="28.0">28</number>
</figureCitation>
), elongate, broader basally than apically, distal margin rounded. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[985,1116,1649,1674]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 30" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1588,1612]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,364,1562]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,347,1565]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 30. Japanagallia neohamata sp. nov. Male: (22 – 23) Habitus: (22) dorsal, and (23) lateral views; (24) face; (25) genital capsule, subgenital plates, and anal tube, lateral view; (26) pygofer posterior margins, caudal view; (27) style, dorsal view; (28) connective, dorsal view; aedeagus (29) lateral, and (30) dorsal views." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/228240/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">
Figs 
<number box="[1042,1116,1650,1674]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139" value="29.5" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="29.0">29–30</number>
</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, with dorsal apodeme elongated and angulate; preatrium well developed and tumid, bearing pair of slender processes on caudal margin, long and directed dorsolaterally; shaft with forked process at base, and respectively with pair of spine-like processes below gonopore on dorsal and ventral margins, dorsal margin sinuate; apical half of shaft elongate, tapered apically beyond gonopore and curved; gonopore subapical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1324,2034]" box="[199,528,1829,1854]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,403,1829,1854]" pageId="6" pageNumber="139">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
